[{'created': '2015-11-03 12:54:12.000000000', 'message': 'VFC Migration mapping string vios reversal

In the case of multiple fabrics with dual vioses, VFC mapping
strings should build mapping across both the VIOSes. So we
need to reverse the vios wraps in order to use the second vios
for the next fabric.

Change-Id: I09d9bd65241195247b326c8afdb54501fd6e4ed9
'}]
commit_message:
VFC Migration mapping string vios reversal

In the case of multiple fabrics with dual vioses, VFC mapping
strings should build mapping across both the VIOSes. So we
need to reverse the vios wraps in order to use the second vios
for the next fabric.

Change-Id: I09d9bd65241195247b326c8afdb54501fd6e4ed9

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 18290, 'date': '2015-11-03 13:42:33.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

Nov 2 10:59 PM	
Stanislaw Bogatkin said:

Sorry, it will never work.

Our Ruby version just can't into TLS higher than v1 - it's a known bug of Ruby itself (commit with 1.1 and 1.2 support was proposed in Ruby v2.2.3 and seem to be never worked properly). It was exact reason why all three version was added here - cause browsers can negotiate on v1.2 but fuel-nailgun-client can't - and it's the reason why there is hardcoded v1 into it also. I check this from time to time - there is no backport yet also, so we must use all three version to not break compatibility. As I dare to say - there is no attacks to v1 that 1.2 isn't vulnerable also."}]

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on py34
we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch
puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem
to happen.
Closes-bug: #1489059
Change-Id: I457bd97b8e34c71300abbf909d459e5583e46927

commit_message:
Convert count value into integer in scaling policy

Sometimes, the count value provided in action input could be string
rather than integer. In that case, we should convert it first
before calculating scaling adjustment in scaling policy.

Change-Id: Ide708fcaa63ad9133f52693484e1f5861be777d3

Thanks Taku for review comments. Please find my comments inline. 

On your comment regarding interface fields in response:

Actually IMO it should return only those fields in the response, values for which are allocated by kuryr. Argument behind this logic is like this, if some fields are coming with non-empty values in request that means IPAM has allocated those values and network driver should not allocate values for these fields. On the other hand, if network driver is allocating values for some field, driver should respond back with this value to libnetwork.
Please see libnetwork code also for respose validation.

[{'created': '2015-10-15 12:27:13.000000000', 'message': "Update devref to catchup with libnetwork 0.5.0

Updating devref to address following changes in libnetwork:
1. Removal of 'service'
2. Vendoring in IPAM driver support from libnetwork to docker. This
allows user to pass subnet of their choice using docker cli.

refer to the links for details:
https://github.com/docker/docker/pull/16645
https://github.com/docker/libnetwork/blob/master/docs/ipam.md

Change-Id: I30f5cb54d4feadafc954f6e4b09bcbd6243e6c00
Closes-Bug: #1505489

commit_message:
Update devref to catchup with libnetwork 0.5.0

Updating devref to address following changes:
1. Removal of 'service' from docker
2. Vendoring in IPAM driver support from libnetwork to docker. This
allows user to pass subnet of their choice using docker cli. In case
if user does not provide subnet related configuration and neither
remote ipam driver while creating network, built-in ipam driver will
provide default subnet configuration.

refer to the links for details:
https://github.com/docker/docker/pull/16645
https://github.com/docker/libnetwork/blob/master/docs/ipam.md

Change-Id: I30f5cb54d4feadafc954f6e4b09bcbd6243e6c00
Closes-Bug: #1505489

commit_message:
Per-branch HEAD files for conflict management

We have pep8 check for validation revisions, but it allows
outdated changes go into merge queue. To prevent this added
CONTRACT_HEAD, EXPAND_HEAD files.

Closes-bug: #1505701

Change-Id: Ie4b727e55a0b1ecb12e915a0037094a928d8f975

[{'created': '2015-10-08 20:02:01.000000000', 'message': 'Replace internal oslo_policy mock with public fixture

This replaces a mock on an internal oslo_policy http class

commit_message:
Drop types module usage

Since python 2.2, use of types module is not prefered way to
access the type hence it is replaced by using names of built-in
factory functions.

Change-Id: Ibdcc1ae75204f67076edab5edcffe94a9f1f1d8e
Implements: blueprint replace-types-module-with-new-style-classes

commit_message:
Move policy detach from action to cluster

This patch moves the policy-detach logic from action to cluster module.
The intent is to simplify the action module while making the operation a
method of the cluster. This logic now can be reused in other context
with a constraint that the cluster must be locked first.

Change-Id: Id0139769e6600d45eac93e37c938c06e0aecfde8

commit_message:
Docs: clarify that AnySubnetRequest is optional

The phrasing of "may not support" was a little confusing, mostly because
I read it as an imperative - "you may not do this" instead of it
being "you can do this if you want"

Change-Id: Ia4fb87a649f1d4bc312f4ad3bb5c2f48a7b6741b

can you please add context to this change so we can review it.  what is the use case? is transport_url new?'}, {'account_id': 8601, 'date': '2015-09-23 10:01:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Sure. No, transport_url is alternative way to configure transport
Also it is primary way. oslo.messaging logic uses it if it is set. If it is not oslo.messaging reads rpc_backend option to choose oslo.messaging driver and uses rpc_backend related options set to get connected (rabbit_host, rabbit_userid, rabbit_password etc)
transport_url agregate all those parameters in single connection string

This patch is not about changing configiration approach from rpc_backend option to transport_url it was only small simplification and moving to primary configuration approach of oslo.messaging. The goal of this patch is to make oslo messaging driver configurable. I'm working on new implementation of messaging driver which will use pika library as rabbitmq client. And I need to be able run devstack test for it.

If switching to transport_url approach is problem somehow I can change patch and just do rpc_backend = $RABBIT_DRIVER instead of rpc_backend = "rabbit"'}, {'account_id': 8601, 'date': '2015-09-28 13:31:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Commit message was updated'}, {'account_id': 13290, 'date': '2015-09-28 13:31:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-28 14:55:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

Please, give us enough context to review this without going on an archaeological dig

As I believe I've found out, the reason behind this is to use "pika" as opposed to "rabbit"/"kombu" because the latter is less maintained.

Please link to [1] and explain this in the commit.  I also think this need some depends-on: on the outstanding changes, because it's not something we want without those committed.  also wants a note in doc/source/configuration where we talk about rpc backends

So given the context of this, and our general unwillingness to re-introduce too many variables in to the RPC path after going to some effort to reduce it in  I8073a895c03ec927a2598eff6c2f01e5c82606fc, I'd prefer to see us checking a externally set value is either rabbit or, i guess, "pika", and throwing an error if it is anything else.  that way we are explict in what we support.

commit_message:
Support for oslo.messaging pika driver for RabbitMQ

Oslo team is writing a new driver for RabbitMQ using
the pika library. We'll need to support switching
between the existing kombu library and the new pika
library based as well to be able to develop and
trouble shoot the new driver. This patch makes it
configurable.

Change-Id: Ie3cb4c2c9868d0c859f1a8dccde44df6f69ceb81
Depends-On: I7bda78820e657b1e97bf888d4065a917eb317cfb
Implements: blueprint configurable-rpc-backend
Implements: blueprint rabbit-pika

commit_message:
Create keystone roles and admin user from t-h-t manifests

Currently keystone initialization happens via os-cloud-config [1].

This commit moves some of that directly into the manifests. This is the
first in a series of two changes to migrate it entirely into t-h-t.

This change focus on implementing what keystone.initialize() was doing
on the tripleoclient [2], creates the admin tenant, user and roles.

It also creates the keystone endpoint itself.

1.  https://github.com/openstack/os-cloud-config/blob/master/os_cloud_config/keystone.py#L128-L158
2.  https://github.com/openstack/python-tripleoclient/blob/master/tripleoclient/v1/overcloud_deploy.py#L462-L527

Change-Id: I98555b707ff9b91c6e218de5dca68106ea05c8ea
Depends-On: Ia4b3244f114dcff746ab89d355ad4933f8fdbddf

commit_message:
Use 'False' as default value for "compression" common capability

Drivers that report no value for the "compression" common capability
should be treated in the scheduler as if compression=False.

Change-Id: I60ebfd24f623ec3da081e48afa39cc5c2fee52b0
Closes-Bug: #1504746
(cherry picked from commit 57a6a6535e97233fc84f2d1e744e502792f9dfd9)

Sergii, I think it is ok to have this fix and remove this deprecation warning from client as well. This fix allows not only fix issue with deprecation warning, it also helps to remove old configuration file and create new one.'}, {'account_id': 11090, 'date': '2015-10-13 12:20:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 26: Code-Review-2

IMO, this should be done in different way (linux way).

client should generate default config if config is not present. if config is present, client will load data from it. 99% of programs use this way.

If we take in account upgrade, config file may contain the version of config, new version of client may load data from config, delete it and generate a new one.

There shouldn't be any hacks to skeleton at all, thus this env variable should be deprecated. Config will be generated on first run of client."}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2015-10-13 12:30:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 26: Code-Review-1

(5 comments)

commit_message:
Added MAINTAINERS to top-level repo directory

In a consensus reached in a proposal for code review process
change [1], and proposed team structure policy document [2],
adding MAINTAINERS files in repositories.

Please note, that this file is written in YAML format in order
to allow further automation around code review process.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-August/072406.html
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/225376/

Fuel-CI: disable

Change-Id: I0090fb3f9bac3a15a28dc11671e8dce0edc2a94b
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
[WIP] do_mkbootstrap

Split do_build_image
Initial commit for nailgun:do_mkbootstrap :
 New entry point, wich add possibility to build
 custom bootstrap image,based on ubuntu-trusty.

Implements: blueprint dynamically-build-bootstrap
Related-Bug: #1444090
Change-Id: I0ea7da105c662940618fd1c120e75d491db9914f

commit_message:
Task status 'pending' handled in tests

Status 'pending' introduced for proper tasks as intermediate status
for tasks ready for sending or already sent to astute, but not
acknoledged by astute. After task is acknoledged by astute it
changes status to 'running'.

Change-Id: Idedb061b7b5c4dca4a0ca7adcaa570cecbb691af
Partial-Bug: #1498827

commit_message:
Produce an error when extra arguments are present

Currently `parse_known_args` method is used which does not produce an
error when extra arguments are present. In this patch `parse_args` is
used which produces an error when extra arguments are present.

Change-Id: Iefbf221d912cce2b2af536f471c89f4a7a49693d
Closes-Bug: #1460572
Closes-Bug: #1496967

commit_message:
Dynamic dnsmasq for fuelweb_admin networks

Install 'daemonize' package in mcollective container for puppet
mcollective agent. Also configure Hiera inside mcollective container.

We need this for puppet task which is being executed in 'mcollective'
container and which updates dnsmasq dhcp ip ranges when we change
fuelweb_admin networks in any nodegroup.

Co-Authored-By: Aleksandr Didenko <adidenko@mirantis.com>

Blueprint: dynamic-dnsmasq
Partial-bug: #1495593

Change-Id: I3309b32e3ede4be2f6758ff756b4ed15e3b20d66

commit_message:
Revert "Move user-defined extra networks from dnsmasq.template to astute"

This reverts commit b59f69257b043212522b3c4fff946bd68068879a.

We're implementing automatic configuration of DHCP ranges in
dnsmasq so this workaround is no longer needed.

Co-Authored-By: Aleksandr Didenko <adidenko@mirantis.com>
Blueprint: dynamic-dnsmasq
Change-Id: I9dc55ff18b6faac36ff7603dffe9de0dcd4ada22

During dev setup in a vm environment, the default OS partitioning
may result in insufficient space for the libvirt default storage
pool which defaults (and we also hard-code) to
/var/lib/libvirt/images

This simple change means you can export LIBVIRT_VOL_POOL_TARGET

commit_message:
Adds LIBVIRT_VOL_POOL_TARGET to tripleo create-nodes

During dev setup in a vm environment, the default OS partitioning
may result in insufficient space for the libvirt default storage
pool which defaults (and we also hard-code) to
/var/lib/libvirt/images

This change means you can export LIBVIRT_VOL_POOL_TARGET
before instack-virt-setup to get the libvirt default storage pool
created there (and the directory is created if necessary).

Change-Id: I85d51457fbd8b747f55091f3ecdc6ca921b70b84

commit_message:
Tidy up docs - fixup missing links to TOC where possible

Due to layout of current docs, some sections don't display the TOC
on the left hand navbar, for example installation/installation.html

One of the reasons is that the subsections there (installing or
updating) are labelled as sections (=== instead of ----).

This updates the installation and troubleshooting sections

commit_message:
CentOS 7: enable network interfaces by default

CentOS 7 has network interfaces disabled by default, using ONBOOT=no configuration parameter for interfaces,
in contrast to the CentOS 6.x default behavior. Due to keep compatibility with the expectations, lets enable
the interfaces.

The other difference is migration to systemd. The script rc.local using for form the /etc/issue should be called
on boot. Corresponding systemd service rc-local.service is called when the /etc/rc.local is executable.
Since the /etc/rc.local file and access rights are changed in the kick-start file, nothing should be done here.

Change-Id: Iccda83f35c0306cefe12e468a73fff4d1aa49f5e
Closes-bug: #1507896

This package uses pbr, which sets "include_package_data=True" and which also populates the MANIFEST file with all files in git. OpenStack releases source tarballs of this repo that have been created using python setup.py sdist in a properly set up git repo. The tarballs produced have the yaml files.

If this is broken in debian, I recommend:
- git import-orig  # to import the orig tarball from upstream
or
- ensuring that the upstream git repo is checked out and then using python setup.py sdist

Can you give me more information on why that is not working for you?'}, {'account_id': 4190, 'date': '2015-09-15 01:08:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Will try to do the work within PBR, so giving up on that one.'}]

commit_message:
Include all yaml files in MANIFEST.in

In Debian, the package misses all yaml files. This patch
fixes the situation by adding a recursive-include.

Change-Id: I3ba4126fe83e03bbfb9aa521b49ef042b200b55c

in Debian.

[{'created': '2015-03-23 22:56:50.000000000', 'message': 'Makes configuration files more standard

In Debian, there's a system to configure the Keystone auth token,
the rabbitmq connection and the database. If you don't know about
it, please read the doc over here:
http://docs.openstack.org/juno/install-guide/install/apt-debian/content/ch_debconf.html

This patch indends to:
- Make the configuration files parseable by Debian's config and postinst
scripts (so that Debconf can be used)
- Make it more "OpenStack standard"

Change-Id: If8607f5071d02965307a1d5b021878cc36637d5e
'}, {'created': '2015-03-24 07:59:13.000000000', 'message': 'Makes configuration files more standard

commit_message:
Makes configuration files more standard

In Debian, there's a system to configure the Keystone auth token,
the rabbitmq connection and the database. If you don't know about
it, please read the doc over here:
http://docs.openstack.org/juno/install-guide/install/apt-debian/content/ch_debconf.html

This patch indends to:
- Make the configuration files parseable by Debian's config and postinst
scripts (so that Debconf can be used)
- Make it more "OpenStack standard"

Change-Id: If8607f5071d02965307a1d5b021878cc36637d5e

commit_message:
Also install alembic migration files

Doing a normal "python setup.py install" doesn't get all the files
installed by default: the files in manila/db/migrations/alembic aren't
included.

In Debian, we have to carry a patch to make all the files from the
alembic migrations folder installed properly. Please add this patch
to the trunk of Manila, so that we don't have to carry it at the
distribution level.

Change-Id: Ic31f426059a2ecb7824833b6ea559ab79fc99ad4

commit_message:
Bump ceilometerclient to 1.4.0

If using something lower than 1.4.0, heat just fails to
pass unit tests. I experienced this when building it for
Debian Experimental.

So this patch bumps the minimum version to 1.4.0.

Change-Id: I672eb3e6f7b6bea6696e62b5553d0f647db1fd26

commit_message:
Use USR2 to create "Guru Meditation Report"

Nova project uses default signal from oslo_reports, and it is USR2 now,
since https://review.openstack.org/223133 is merged.
USR1 just terminates nova-compute.

commit_message:
Add support to stack update

This patch adds support to update operation for Heat stacks. Heat
returns a 202 for update operation, so this needs a special handler.

Change-Id: I21a3ba5b4f50252e5be62488f25dac41ff438460

commit_message:
archive_policy: disallow to have identical granularities

This disallows having several identical granularities in an archive policy.
This makes sure that when you pick an granularity requested by the user we
can't pick the "wrong" archive, e.g. the longer or shorter one for example.

Change-Id: I937f464d09514741f7ede505b8d7c507ce466c2d

This seems like the right thing to do but it does raise an interesting UX question: Is it not now possible for me to throw measures at gnocchi and have them be accepted but never stored because I forgot to create the resource in the first place?

When would I find out about my mistake?'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2015-11-02 14:43:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Chris no, because actually the metric existence is validated before in the chain, by querying the indexer.

Now the storage driver just blindly accepts new measurements because it trusts that the indexer did the check before. If the metric has been removed in the meantime, or is removed later, anyway the measurements will  be deleted by metricd.'}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2015-11-02 14:45:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

commit_message:
rest: add_measures never raises MetricDoesNotExist

This is not true anymore since Gnocchi has been made asynchronous for
its measures processing.

Change-Id: I63967cfc4a58dad5630cda1d6dbd43a6d31291d1

API resource names should not include underscores

As a guideline from API WG, API resource names should not include
underscores, maybe we should modify some resource names.

commit_message:
rest: do not store empty measure set

If the measure set is empty, there's no need to store and process it
later. Just do nothing.

Change-Id: I52f84bc259485c47344fba985d6cc1cd82e599ae
Related-Bug: #1511656

carbonara: handle empty update

nothing.

commit_message:
api: use Paste to deploy WSGI server

This allows to tweak the middleware pipeline in the same way than other
OpenStack projects.

Closes-Bug: #1504130

commit_message:
Adding get_resource_id method to CLI utils

This method provides a small optimisation in
case we don't need anything else but resource
id, allowing not to request a resource when we
already have an id.

Partially implements: blueprint cli-as-openstackclient-plugin

Change-Id: I44baf18e5b1a1dc61948674ae4dbe1bb4cbed08d

commit_message:
Set swift_partition to /var/lib/glance/node by default

We had an ability to set swift partition in modular
script, but it was removed in this commit:
Ia2428b49a7192a2d7d56ffdc61a75de9ebc816c9

We should use /var/lib/glance/node as swift partition
by default as it was before and provide access
to this folder for swift user.
Also noop tests were added to cover this parameter.

Change-Id: Ic38c726d5ae9fff1815e6a8b4158549c09cec84c
Closes-bug: #1508482

commit_message:
Remove exit code verification from MySQL OCF

Without set -o pipefail exit code of pipeline operations reports of last
operation. This change removes exit code verification to make it POSIX
compliant

Issue was introduced by Ia7670a4f1b8540f6ac9ca8ff66dabd36e7f8738a

Change-Id: Ief67bb96c7806011e246597cf1f46b88613981ea
Closes-Bug: 1505735
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
[Ironic] Add baremetal network for ironic

This change adds:
* neutron serializer for 8.0
* ability to set network group optional
* new optional baremetal network
* transformations for Ironic
* new predefined network for Neutron

Ironic requires separate baremetal network on infra nodes and neutron flat
network mapped to this physical network.

New baremetal network is optional and depends on Ironic component enabled in
settings. Predefined network for neutron is optional too.

Until optional networks is not supported in common way, this change introduces
a workaround to get baremetal network optional.

Change-Id: I95570df5d986e5f3a97ca21711d31d0e8ed817fd
Implements: blueprint fuel-integrate-ironic (partially)

commit_message:
compute: make re-schedule working when resize fails

The design intends to catch every host error exceptions and then
reschedule for resize/migrate however since the rpc is using a
"cast" it would return before to wait the response and make the
process of re-schedule when a fail not possible.

This commit updates the rpc to use a "call" which will wait until the
process is terminated before to continue.

Change-Id: I7ba0ba4a8952eadb25b1ee0fece2d12a2010e848
Closes-Bug: #1263044

commit_message:
Fix noVNC console access for an IPv6 setup

Following a recent change in websocket proxy code
(commit: fdb73a2d445971c6158a80692c6f74094fd4193a),
novnc console access is not working for IPv6 addresses.
This patch fixes the issue by taking into account the way
IPv6 urls are constructed and parsing them accordingly.

(cherry picked from commit 30fe27dd3f4d8f53981c2162f1e34b837d3c6437)

Closes-Bug: #1456963
Change-Id: Ia6c50be1e3cbe8a21f0a75b6a7cebd1712d311f8

commit_message:
compute: update refresh network info logic

Currently periodic task runs by default every 60 seconds.
The first call is to load a list of running instances from the
database then every 60 seconds 1 instance is updated until the
list is empty.
This logic takes in the worst case for a host with 40 instances
41 minutes to have all cache refreshed.

The new logic will try to update more intance caches per periodic
task cycle without to stress to much the database and neutron if
configured. Basically if configured by default it should be able
to update all cache in two/three cycles.

Change-Id: I7098f27dcde649d66eaf28accb136706bf12592d

Rephrase comments for Share create API

This is a trivial fix to rephrase two comments that were copied from
cinder v2 Volume API in manila v1 Share API as they are quite
confusing.

commit_message:
Add retries and timeouts for openstack commands

Add retries for each idempotent command in openstack
provider and add timeouts for all commands.

Upstream review: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/220224/

Change-Id: I4d1947a9a76f9a26f0bbc49a871fb1d0298d5bdc
Closes-bug: #1507685

commit_message:
Enable decimal value for $DIB_IMAGE_SIZE.

Patch adds support for using decimal values for $DIB_IMAGE_SIZE.
This allows for creating images that are <1G in size.

Change-Id: I945644a8e77fecfb0b83efa282dc00bb29514e0b
Closes-Bug: #1366909

commit_message:
Use dict comprehension

As python 2.6 is not supported any more, we should use 
dict comprehension for concise code.

Change-Id: Ic06fa7acd9f60674ea4627581cdc878319e23412

commit_message:
Use assertTrue/False instead of assertEqual(T/F)

The usage of assertEqual(True/False, ***) should be changed
to a meaningful format of assertTrue/False(***).
This patch fixes the same in Manila.

Change-Id: I0623c17a939e5175c15986dc7b6b64114c346c78
Closes-Bug: #1512207

commit_message:
Add ability to support discard/unmap/trim for Cinder backend

Currently, libvirt/qemu has support for a discard option when
attaching a volume to an instance. With this feature, the
unmap/trim command can be sent from guest to the physical
storage device. A cinder back-end will report a connection
capability that Nova will use in attaching a volume.

Change-Id: I4acb9dbb3c239c1b6b94dca3d2ab438296685a33
Implements: bp cinder-backend-report-discard

commit_message:
Adding Cloudify apps library and Example App

Cloudify Application library package required for all Cloudify applications.
Example Application is for people to try it out in their murano instance.

Partially-Implements: Blueprint support-tosca-cloudify-format
Change-Id: I877423e53d93e3062ed34f7de4d0a33f9093ac0a

subject: Adding the Cloudify Plugin Files

commit_message:
Implementing ONOS ML2 plugin support

This patch developes a plugin library for Open Network Operating System
(ONOS) using neutron ML2 MechanismDriver. This plugin will handle the back-end
communication of neutron with Open Network Operating System (ONOS) controller
using ReST calls.

Change-Id: I6c7f930c0d7975e9a8efbcd207b3a6c7e04011e9
Closes-Bug: #1474240
Co-Authored-By: dongfeng <albert.dongfeng@huawei.com>

When you request the token by using the POST method with V3/auth/tokens the path, and the request body includes a payload of credentials including the authentication method and, optionally, the authorization scope,(The scope includes either a project or domain.) and if everything is right, the response you get, which should contain the metadata of 'extras'. Change-Id: Ia035540382a1c0a9bc8770b062ac48328bff0a18
'}]
commit_message:
Update certain TokenAuth Responses of V3

When you request the token by using the POST method with V3/auth/tokens the path, and the request body includes a payload of credentials including the authentication method and, optionally, the authorization scope,(The scope includes either a project or domain.) and if everything is right, the response you get, which should contain the metadata of 'extras'. (Just like '"extras":""',in json format.)So, TokenAuthNoScopeResponse.json, TokenAuthScopeDomainResponse.json, and TokenAuthScopeProjectResponse.json shold be updated.

Change-Id: Ia035540382a1c0a9bc8770b062ac48328bff0a18

commit_message:
Drop periodic jobs for oslo-incubator

We don't have a stable/liberty branch for liberty so
we don't need this job (and the job is failing)

Change-Id: I92bfadf275010193cb43d1b96ad31781b5c9aeef

commit_message:
Add dsvm gate job to freezer-api

We need to execute integration tests
automatically at every commit in the
freezer-api repo. This commit add
the dsvm gate job to the project.

Change-Id: I377f3632dd7dccc762a8370d433e14e0d48f414f

commit_message:
Add note about vmware_linked_clone when spawning with ISO

On refacrctoring on image user function for spawn(), adding reason why
and condition where vmware_linked_clone property is ignored when
spawning with ISO image.

Closes-Bug: #1366325

Change-Id: Icde3817189b64215d8203bd32217439c7a11403a
Signed-off-by: Masaki Furuta <masaki.furuta@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Fix calling delete_zones method with a wrong argument

Add a new zone with cisco zonemanager driver. If the added zone
name is the same as the existed name, the function delete_zones
will be called. But it fails because of passing a argument with
incorrect type. This patch fixes this error.

Co-Authored-By: Al Lau <alau2@cisco.com>
Closes-Bug: #1496283
Change-Id: Ib340b6828cfeb2bb318db23971268c7974ecc9f6

commit_message:
lvconvert missing from cinder volume.filters

The LVM lvconvert command is invoked by the revert method of the
cinder.brick.local_dev.lvm.LVM class but was missing a matching
volume.filters CommandFilter entry which has now been added.

Change-Id: Ib436f562a6dd7b8828e34051b5d73273c1f52b50
Closes-Bug: 1510654

Using a PREFIX of MII the size is limited to about 16000

Shortening the check to only MI increases the size of tokens
to the point where the size will not be possible to fill.

The drawback is the MI is more likely to get a false positive against any
block, including an ASN1 document of different length.  However,
this is not a practical issue, as the token would still be rejected.

Closes-Bug: 1240163

commit_message:
Shorten PKI Token Identifier to MI

Using a PREFIX of MII the size is limited to about 16000

Shortening the check to only MI increases the size of tokens
to the point where the size will not be possible to fill.

The drawback is the MI is more likely to get a false positive against any
block, including an ASN1 document of different length.  However,
this is not a practical issue, as the token would still be rejected.

Co-Authored-By: Henrique Truta <henrique@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>

Change-Id: Id0f1cbf5082e10abe0fcb7a887f0b6197ade429e
Closes-Bug: 1240163

commit_message:
Add "agent_wol" (AgentAndWakeOnLanDriver)

This patch adds new driver with WakeOnLanPower and AgentDeploy
interfaces. Automatic deploy is possible because AgentDeploy
does soft power off at the end of deploy cycle.

Change-Id: I09dc41c1523fafc5155a02829f9528d65cf2f5b0

commit_message:
Fix StrOpt to allow setting quotes and regex

StrOpt can't setting quotes and regex. Even it can't support latest
feature of ignore_case.

StrOpt only assign choice argument to types.String. And then pass remain
arguments to parent class. But parent class's parameter don't have
quotes, regex or ignore_case parameters. Therefore StrOpt will raise
exception about unexpected keyword argument.

Change-Id: Icda911de28f8d8d786daed137dd5d76febd6ad3e
Closes-Bug: 1508800

commit_message:
Remove reference to undefined attributes

is_user_context refers to a user_id and project_id attribute in
the context object which are not defined in this base class.

Change-Id: I2ac6d4a7d31d026e6fedcba80c4a760dcac747e8
Closes-Bug: 1508217

commit_message:
Change assertTrue(isinstance()) by optimal assert

Some of tests use different method of assertTrue(isinstance(A, B)).
The correct way is to use assertIsInstance(A, B) provided by testtools.

Closes-bug: #1268480
Change-Id: I9532fa65a939767e13e0917a77d4698bf74d3ca6

commit_message:
Bump minimum Django version

Django 1.7 will reach end of support during the M development cycle. It
should be dropped from requirements before M release.

https://www.djangoproject.com/download/#supported-versions

Add murano projects to PROJECTS variable in murano job template

Job gate-tempest-dsvm-murano-cfapi fails because murano-related projects
doesn't added to PROJECTS variable.
This patch add murano, murano-dashboard and python-muranoclient.

[{'created': '2015-11-02 17:13:37.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "Add 'X-Auth-Token' default header to CORS middleware"

The existence of this header is not tested, and therefore can
create fragility downstream as operators deploying an API
may not realize that this setting is needed. If the upstream
library is ever updated to remove this, all downstream projects
will silently fail.

Furthermore, the addition of openstack-specific headers as
defaults in this library makes oslo_middleware less useful
outside of openstack.

The correct way to address this issue is to enable latent
configuration from paste.ini. This way, each service can
include their default headers in their packaged paste file.

This reverts commit 562173aeb7839eaca6274531b0e91147941af6df.

Change-Id: I401011ed055fea49268686deb5c25f02d2ca6164
'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Add 'X-Auth-Token' default header to CORS middleware"

The existence of this header is not tested, and therefore can
create fragility downstream as operators deploying an API
may not realize that this setting is needed. If the upstream
library is ever updated to remove this, all downstream projects
will silently fail.

Furthermore, the addition of openstack-specific headers as
defaults in this library makes oslo_middleware less useful
outside of openstack.

The correct way to address this issue is to enable latent
configuration from paste.ini. This way, each service can
include their default headers in their packaged paste file.

This reverts commit 562173aeb7839eaca6274531b0e91147941af6df.

Change-Id: I401011ed055fea49268686deb5c25f02d2ca6164

commit_message:
Add IPDevice.exists() method

Some callers of ip_lib.device_exists() have already instantiated
an IPDevice object, let's move the device existence check into
the IPDevice class so they can call it directly.

Change-Id: I3cdcd0a86b77e1fd5a808b7a5f0de2057f1e90c1
(cherry picked from commit 164502389c15a25a1f3ece51e3760b1b815ed42c)

commit_message:
Filter is converted to list.

In py34 while getting final state, task state turned
into error.
In py34 filter() returns iterator so it will be never
empty or None and that is the reason why task state is
error every time.

Change-Id: I73d5542b82ac8d74e31c64746ae14173536e6eb4

UI: Execution Overview screen refactored

* added new fields: creation time,
  time since creation, time since update,
  description, state info
* added iso filter to time fields
* refactored layout

screenshot: http://pasteboard.co/1JWCLz3B.png

Partially implements blueprint: mistral-dashboard-executions-screen

Change-Id: I4eb20fd57895450e7d488efd4b4a55dcd5aaae06

+1 to Sean's comment, but, as we have bug that could leave instance in db in inconsistent state seems to be ok to merge that as a hotfix.
Jamie, I've got question about locking: if one of the threads notice that token become invalid it'll try to get new one, doing this witin a lock.
What if n thread(say 1000) noticed that token is invalid? Could such  synchronization become a bottleneck? Is it also mean that all thread starts to invalidate one token after another, so we'll get ~1000 invalid tokens, while it should be enough to make one invalidate call?"}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2015-09-15 00:34:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Timofey, 

I'm not sure it'd be any more of a bottleneck than it is today. Actually what the current lock and this one would do is prevent all 1000 threads deciding they need a new token at once and all fetching it. 

Assumedly the lock would be held for the same amount of time it would take for this next thread to also go and fetch a token and we ensure that it is only fetched once.

Note that i think this won't merge in favour of the same idea managed by keystoneclient: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/221738/"}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2015-09-15 00:36:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Note regarding invalidation, all invalidating does is remove the existing token from the auth plugin. The actual work of fetching a new token is handled by the next request for the token so 1000 invalidates is no big deal so long as we only have one authenticatoin.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-16 08:41:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change or one of its cross-repo dependencies was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of its repository. Please rebase the change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2015-11-03 03:42:53.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Implemented in keystoneclient/keystoneauth'}]

commit_message:
Put a lock around fetching a token

If we put a shim in that activates a lock around all the functions that
can fetch a new token then we can use the same plugin across all threads
and not worry about the reauthentication behaviour.

Change-Id: Ib9805ec6184fb623d4c6b2fa68a0cc0f5c90ccb8

commit_message:
More specific error checking

Narrow the scope of the general except handler block. For offline
validation there are only CMS validation errors or Invalid tokens we
should need to handle.

Change-Id: If11d7011f3827290726ac2918000a38b703d332a

commit_message:
make intermediary.sh support stable branches

The Ironic team has some liberty stable releases to create, but the
intermediary script takes actions it should not for stable branches.
Update the script accordingly.

Change-Id: Ibc4b99b10a503cdcfddfcfe9b6fc3c8a3c76f66f

I'm not sure how I feel about the current naming of utils.py but we do seem to have a few utils.py files in our test directories.

What if instead of renaming the file so that it doesn't clash with test_<file-name-from-code>, we start some naming convention for the test file used to test that testing code.

Eg, instead of 'test_utils.py', because we assume test_<something> is a filename in the code, we do something like 'test_foo_utils.py'. Ok, I'm joking, how about 'test_this_utils.py' or 'test_test_utils.py' or 'test__utils.py'? FWIW, I thought I'd look at nova cuz they are smart like us, and I saw 'test_test_utils.py'. I kind of like the double underscore myself :D"}, {'account_id': 14760, 'date': '2015-10-22 21:15:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

As far as this specific file, it seemed like almost all imports of it were:

 from ironic.tests.unit.conductor import utils as mgr_utils

So renaming it to just mgr_utils seems like a good idea, to me :)

Now maybe we should call the test file something like one of the following:

commit_message:
Rename utils.py to mgr_utils.py to avoid namespace collision

The file ironic/tests/unit/conductor/utils.py is used during testing but
there is also an ironic/conductor/utils.py and then it is confusing
which test_* file belongs to which file.

Rename utils.py to mgr_utils.py and rename the test file

Intentionally not renaming test_conductor_utils.py to test_utils.py at
this time as we would lose git history for the files. This is best done
in a follow-up patch.

Updated all import statements for unit tests using this file.

Change-Id: I5dfa1ffc01c5f54dc41a7caed83cd0bca3fb0be6

commit_message:
Add volume type to create server API

Currently in create server API, using block_device_mapping
parameter can create cinder volume and attach to instance, but there
aren't volume type parameter to create a SLA based volume, so
this bp will add the volume type to create api.

Change-Id: I11e70d30c3e7f3346a31151ea1ab48c40cf0c7bc
Blueprint: enable-volume-types

commit_message:
Don't wrap wrapped exceptions in operatorcloud.py

Similar to change Ia1e45f4971f4b51f28538260d64f778aecaa6f3d
If we've wrapped the exception because of Auth things, we don't need
to re-wrap it - it's just confusing.

Change-Id: Iecbe4137acc2b27848b09e415df35d486f92c951

commit_message:
Use assertIn and assertNotIn

Tests should use:
  self.assertIn(value, list)
  self.assertNotIn(value, list)

instead of:
  self.assertTrue(value in list)
  self.assertFalse(value in list)

because assertIn and assertNotIn raise more meaningful errors:
  self.assertIn(3, [1, 2])
  >>> MismatchError: 3 not in [1, 2]

  self.assertTrue(3 in [1, 2])
  >>> AssertionError: False is not true

Closes-Bug: #1510007
Change-Id: If33252cc93c06a85e61871fb7b22b726f4a08500

Sripriya - i don't think that number matter here for positive cases. The recheck happens every 1s while waiting for DEAD state. If the vnf doesn't go to DEAD within 300s we mark the testcase failed. These long timeouts is minor inconvenience only for failure scenarios."}, {'account_id': 17952, 'date': '2015-10-23 23:38:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 17952, 'date': '2015-10-23 23:40:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Thank you for writing the tests Santosh!'}, {'account_id': 13485, 'date': '2015-10-23 23:47:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

@Sridhar from the logs I have seen where vnf has respawned 49 - 50 times before hitting the dead status in time out loop. This has happened because the transition from dead to active happens so fast that it catches the dead status at only certain point of time when the query matches the vnf status. By then the device would have respawned like 50 times and see 50 dead device id's in vnf dictionary."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-24 00:02:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

Either case, the code change looks harmless.

commit_message:
build-images: Add support for docker base images

DIB recently got some new capabilities to help build
docker images. This patch updates build-images so
that it supports:

 -skip_base: to skip the 'base' element if you wish to do so
 -docker_target: the name of the docker target to create
 - the type option is properly passed into DIB so that it
   doesn't always default to qcow.

Using these new build-images options it is should be possible
to create .yaml files that help define how to build docker
images.

Change-Id: I9b9464c88bb6ce2914cd499ba4fe207ce355bf70
Depends-On: Ib60db3b717d33d4cf3181d70fe0ffbfa86fd5d02

commit_message:
Add migrating of legacy routers to L3 HA docs

Following the patch on which this patch depends on, migrating of legacy
routers to L3 HA in Neutron will be available. As such, documentations
are in order, and those are included here.

Related-Bug: #1365426
Closes-Bug: #1509583
Change-Id: I7ed474516670fd932051d63db6b440fca1e24a19

commit_message:
test_db_base_plugin_v2: Skip a few tests on some platforms

netaddr (and its underlying libc inet_pton) produces different
representations of IPv4-compat addresses for different platforms.

Linux:
    >>> netaddr.IPAddress("::2")
    IPAddress('::2')
    >>>

OSX:
    >>> netaddr.IPAddress("::2")
    IPAddress('::0.0.0.2')
    >>>

As our API assumes Linux's way, skip affected test cases on
the other platforms.

Conflicts:
	neutron/tests/tools.py

Related-Bug: #1484837
Change-Id: I89e1822bb92dfcf8772bba1a3edf908c89550119

commit_message:
Set security group provider rule for icmpv6 RA in DVR

Security group provider rules for RA is set for the VM ports
when a router interface is added or updated after the VM
instance is created.

In the case of DVR Routers the security group provider rule
to allow the RA packets to flow through the VM port input
chain was missing and so the VM was not able to get a
SLAAC/DHCP address when associated with a DVR Router.

This fix will add the security group rule to the VM port input
chain to allow the RA packets to flow into the VM and hence
the VM will obtain an IP address assigned by the Router.

Closes-Bug: #1501969

Conflicts:
	neutron/db/securitygroups_rpc_base.py

Change-Id: Ib0b3499d9c880fe1462734b2d4092debf4819509
(cherry picked from commit a7dc528c1860f6a325a36bb7c633c60b635fc9a6)

commit_message:
Resubmit of "Remove bridge cleanup call" fix

This commit reintroduces the "Remove bridge cleanup call" fix which
was accidentally reverted in a later change:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/209708/

The original description for this fix is:

Remove the bridge cleanup call to delete bridges, since we are seeing
race conditions where bridges are deleted, then new interfaces are
created and are attempting to plug into the bridge before it is
recreated.

Change-Id: I10ffb8fc295bbcc0f9c1a9597ae0b9272ed69c18
Closes-Bug: #1328546
Co-Authored-By: Sean M. Collins <sean@coreitpro.com>
Co-Authored-By: Jordan Callicoat <jordan.callicoat@rackspace.com>

Remove environment_version ref from quickstart guide

This updates the horizon quickstart guide to remove the reference to
the environment_version variable in the run_tests.sh file. This no
longer exists.

Closes-Bug: #1511790

commit_message:
Add vmware insecure and ca_file option in localrc

Adds iniset option for VMWAREAPI_INSECURE and VMWAREAPI_CA_FILE
option to localrc. If a user specified VMWAREAPI_INSECURE=True
in localrc, this patch propogates that by setting insecure=True
option in nova.conf. Similary user can specify certificate path
using VMWAREAPI_CA_FILE directive.

Change-Id: I05ee01ef2249cfd9f0b4dabbbee120c68e07177b

commit_message:
Handle pre-replace and pre-rollback actions

Add try/catch logic in update, which catch all UpdateReplace exceptions.
If UpdateReplace is caught during update, method prepare_for_replace
will be called to prepare resource for replace.
If update happened as part of Rollback, then restore_after_rollback will
be called to restore resource after failed action and prepare for
correct rollback.

commit_message:
workflow.js should be named as workflow.module.js

According to Horizon's angular code file naming convention, a JS file
that defines a new angular module should be named as xxx.module.js so
that it can be correctly sorted in JS file list.

Change-Id: I2290907ae26b6e79a1dcdef788f89584e0698dea
Closes-Bug: #1507043

commit_message:
Disable reloading of a page the user is already on

With Django, a modal spinner would be spawned when a link is
clicked on in the navigation bar. The spinner would be
dismissed after the page refreshed. In the case of the new
angular panels, this refresh never occurs. This fix stops
the page refresh and modal spinner from being displayed
on an already active page.

Fixes bug 1501937

commit_message:
Add documentation for Nimble-Cinder driver

This patch adds documentation for the Nimble Cinder driver.
It specifies the functionalities supported by the driver and
the configuration options available.

Change-Id: I87db992dfc98ae4bab1f5de81c1a9950c31422d8
Closes-Bug: #1506248

commit_message:
Improve bond configuration saving for CentOS7/RHEL7

*Add support of OVS bond configuration saving
*Implement such bond parameters as ad_select, updelay and downdelay for lnx
provider
*Refactor formating and parsing bond options
*Test coverage

Change-Id: I7cf1311f82c6aee980cb5d338ee7f2c0504418d6
Closes-bug: #1510090

subject: Add when DHCP should be enabled for an external network
messages:
[{'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-10-13 13:03:47.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-10-13 13:07:51.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 9515, 'date': '2015-10-13 13:27:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

None of these scenarios support booting VMs on the external network.'}, {'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-10-13 13:58:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Hi Matthew. 

Sure, that is correct. I think the note is to explain that DHCP is usually set to false except for certain scenario. It is in the context where an external network is being created and DHCP is false.

I would appreciate if you could provide suggeestion(s) for better context in the documentation than here.

Thanks,
Martin'}, {'account_id': 9515, 'date': '2015-10-13 14:10:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I'd consider one of the following approaches:

1) Provide a general note near the beginning of the scenario saying that it does not support booting VMs on the external network.
2) Provide a more detailed note near the external subnet creation step saying something like "This subnet explicitly disables DHCP because it does not support attaching VMs directly to it."

Ideally, we need to update these scenarios to support attaching VMs to both the external/public and internal/private networks.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-13 16:44:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-openstack-manuals-tox-checkniceness http://logs.openstack.org/96/234196/2/check/gate-openstack-manuals-tox-checkniceness/3ed0e3c/ : SUCCESS in 2m 54s
- gate-openstack-manuals-tox-checkdeletions http://logs.openstack.org/96/234196/2/check/gate-openstack-manuals-tox-checkdeletions/f407503/ : SUCCESS in 2m 42s
- gate-openstack-manuals-tox-doc-publish-checkbuild http://docs-draft.openstack.org/96/234196/2/check/gate-openstack-manuals-tox-doc-publish-checkbuild/8fc0683//publish-docs/ : SUCCESS in 11m 41s'}, {'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-10-16 16:06:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Workflow-1

@Salvatore: I have chatted with Matthew on IRC and he made a point that if the current scenario does not support booting VMs on the public/ext network, should we tell people that it might. Do we need to add scenarios which boot VMs on external network?'}, {'account_id': 9515, 'date': '2015-10-16 16:16:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Docs mailing list post regarding this topic...

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-docs/2015-October/007671.html'}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2015-10-16 16:26:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I think Matthew is right that in those scenarios you are not supposed to boot vms on external networks. My suggestion was indeed to just remark that DHCP should always be disabled when creating the external network (which is the way these scenarios are configured anyway).

I don't think we need a scenario for booting VMs directly on an external network, at least not at this stage. This might be a future interesting pure IPv6 scenario, but the networking-guide team surely has more valuable input on this matter."}, {'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-10-16 16:39:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Salvatore: WRT bug 1046121, do you think something should be added to the networking docs?'}, {'account_id': 9551, 'date': '2015-11-02 21:12:16.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Talked with Salvatore on IRC. His response is as follows: "I think for the time being you can safely abandon that patch. The note you added does not apply as those scenarios do not encompass booting on external networks, and the networking guide team is not planning at the moment on adding a scenario where you can boot on ext nets".'}, {'account_id': 9515, 'date': '2015-11-02 21:14:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Actually, we are planning to enable attaching VMs to public networks during the Mitaka cycle... likely augmenting the existing scenarios.'}]

commit_message:
Add when DHCP should be enabled for an external network

Usually DHCP is not enabled on an external network. There is howevere
a scenario when instances are deployed on the external network. This
fix is to document it in the networking guide for user undersatnding.

Change-Id: I027c913444b8461fe094a70395a93e3070f16908
Closes-Bug: #1046121

commit_message:
Remove quotes from subshell call in bash script

Always no quotes for $() statement.

We don't need quotes to hold blanks in result:
 # i=$(echo 1 2 3)
 # echo $i
 1 2 3
 #

These quotes can make something wrong in some case:
 # i=$(echo '!')
 #
 # i="$(echo '!')"
 -bash: !: event not found
 #

No real problem for current code, only to use a better code style.

Change-Id: I5909636bdc8de3d44a305d033c8c892af446acf3
Signed-off-by: Zhao Lei <zhaolei@cn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
gerrit: create puppet-keystone-core group

The goal of this patch is to create a Gerrit group that is called
puppet-keystone-core.

This group will include puppet-manager-core (current Puppet OpenStack
core reviewers) and allow to add specific people to puppet-keystone-core
group, who won't be core on other Puppet OpenStack modules.

Change-Id: I6292c04e841740c55fc11261d7fb84faf75c145c

[{'created': '2015-10-08 18:24:35.000000000', 'message': 'VPNaaS: Template based functional jobs

This commit has three goals. First, is to introduce new dsvm based jobs,
so that they can be tested non-voting, without affecting existing jobs
which are voting. Currently, we have jobs in the experimental queue for
neutron, but we cannot move them to the check queue, as those jobs are
voting.

Second, to have the jobs using the same "target names" that are passed
to the hook scripts and used by tox.ini, so that these new jobs could
be used with older releases, once they are voting and replace the old
jobs (which have the same functionality).

Third, to use a single job template that is parameterized, rather that
separated templates that duplicate a lot of logic.

The new jobs are named (the target names in brackets):

gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[dsvm-functional]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[dsvm-functional-sswan]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[api]

They are equivalents to (target names in brackets):

gate-neutron-vpnaas-[dsvm-functional]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-[dsvm-functional-sswan]
gate=neutron-vpnaas-test-dsvm-[api]

Note: the API job is still experimental and was using the new job template.
The job was renamed, so that the target name remained the same, rather than
changing it to 'dsvm-api'.

The expectation is that commit Ieea93753e352ccb09f65aac12c8c81c1d96593ac
will be changed to depend on this change, and will move the jobs to the
check queue, non-voting (once this commit has been tested and upstreamed).

Change-Id: Ie148f895e89f81a5f2e25b5edf609d1b178752bf

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Template based functional jobs

This commit has three goals. First, is to introduce new dsvm based jobs,
so that they can be tested non-voting, without affecting existing jobs
which are voting. Currently, we have jobs in the experimental queue for
neutron, but we cannot move them to the check queue, as those jobs are
voting.

Second, to have the jobs using the same "target names" that are passed
to the hook scripts and used by tox.ini, so that these new jobs could
be used with older releases, once they are voting and replace the old
jobs (which have the same functionality).

Third, to use a single job template that is parameterized, rather that
separated templates that duplicate a lot of logic.

The new jobs are named (the target names in brackets):

gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[dsvm-functional]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[dsvm-functional-sswan]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-test-[api]

They are equivalents to (target names in brackets):

gate-neutron-vpnaas-[dsvm-functional]
gate-neutron-vpnaas-[dsvm-functional-sswan]
gate=neutron-vpnaas-test-dsvm-[api]

Note: the API job is still experimental and was using the new job template.
The job was renamed, so that the target name remained the same, rather than
changing it to 'dsvm-api'.

The expectation is that commit Ieea93753e352ccb09f65aac12c8c81c1d96593ac
will be changed to depend on this change, and will move the jobs to the
check queue, non-voting (once this commit has been tested and upstreamed).

Change-Id: Ie148f895e89f81a5f2e25b5edf609d1b178752bf
Partial-bug: 1495584

commit_message:
Simplify parameters for rpc_backend

It is not needed anymore to specify the whole python namespace
for the backends, and in Liberty this option is completely removed
(see https://review.openstack.org/189201).

This patch keeps backwards compatibility with the previous default
parameters.

Change-Id: I5c84def51bcda593c89c3897c52fb4e8e663e121
(cherry picked from commit 56cacb4a65ffa1bd795cbdbffef4c2071a54a411)

commit_message:
macros/puppet-prepare-node: drop rdo-release

When running Puppet jobs, RDO repository is managed by Puppet.
If rdo-release package is installed, we will always install Liberty
(latest rdo-release package) and we don't want that.
Puppet CI is currently deploying Liberty in stable/kilo jobs, because of
this package.

We need to drop this package before any Puppet related job, so we make
sure Puppet manifests will manage the repositories that we actually want.

Change-Id: I3173e850dfdf43b868e4a180083c19c3cbe30ff3

commit_message:
lib/nova: Remove 'DEFAULT/verbose'

The 'verbose' option has been deprecated by oslo_log. Using it
results in a warning for the 'nova-manage' command and likely
many other OpenStack commands.

Change-Id: Icc11b25f56ebc62443c6afa90b9572d5c63b3882
Partial-bug: #1511505

132fbcd38ebae52bdd20da54905131b75581520f in cinder changed the

commit_message:
Remove CINDER_VOLUME_CLEAR value validation

132fbcd38ebae52bdd20da54905131b75581520f in cinder changed the
volume_clear StrOpt to use the choices kwarg which enforces the value
specified and raises a ValueError if an invalid value is set for the
option in cinder.conf.

This lets us remove the validation that devstack was doing.

Change-Id: Ia7eead6297ed0f3a972de2021170fe9c7225e856

commit_message:
RDO: ensure rdo-release is not installed

Because rdo-release might already been provided by distros, we need to
make sure the package is not installed, otherwise this module will
install a repo maybe older than the one installed by rdo-release.

Example: if you try to install the kilo repo, the rdo-release will
install liberty (because it's the latest), so we need to make sure we
drop the package and let Puppet manage the repo.

Change-Id: I80dcaf4cacbf12176ceeba36ddb740e93086c5d7

Correct the Karma conf to search correct dirs

Changes the basepath and other paths to allow for correct specification
of template dirs, etc.

Closes-Bug: 1507703

commit_message:
Disable command run under root user

Running openstack command with python-tripleoclient under
root user is not supported and should not be allowed. Added
check for user and exit if it is root (EUID=0) to openstack
undercloud install command.

Each command can be disabled for root by adding
utils.ensure_run_as_normal_user() into it's body.

Change-Id: I685c639e02790483d1607c7eac038f8b9b8dc99e
Closes-Bug: rhbz#1239088

Augment the developing_elements.rst by taking advantage of Sphinx
markup. Most of the doc used to be in /README.md and thus did not
leverage on Sphinx.

Use inline codeblock to denote variables, files, command: ``foo``

  List phase names in the preliminary introduction

bottom of the document.

Change-Id: I2421f76ec452cac243ccb2208f88c7d320ffedd3
'}]
commit_message:
Prettify 'Developing Elements' documentation

Augment the developing_elements.rst by taking advantage of Sphinx
markup. Most of the doc used to be in /README.md and thus did not
leverage on Sphinx.

Use inline codeblock to denote variables, files, command: ``foo``
Phase Subdirectories:
  List phase names in the preliminary introduction
  Get rid of lists in favor of definitions
  Highlight whether the phase runs in or outside the chroot
  Input parameters are now lists

Use definition lists in Dependencies and Ramdisk sections.

Link to elements README when they exist.

Testing Element: split into two subsections: 'shell' and 'python'.

Use "sourcecode:: sh" for the couple examples at the very top and very
bottom of the document.

Change-Id: I2421f76ec452cac243ccb2208f88c7d320ffedd3

[{'created': '2015-11-02 15:40:15.000000000', 'message': 'Multipath commands with error messages in stdout fail to parse

This change fixes an issue in find_multipath_device() where the command
output of multipath -l <device> would sometimes fail to be parsed if
there were error messages in the stdout string in addition to the
expected output. We will now strip out the error messages before we
attempt to parse the lines.

NOTE(lyarwood): This is a simple port of the change already present
in Cinder for Kilo. This is no longer required on master for Nova due
to the move to os-brick.

Multipath commands with error messages in stdout fail to parse
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/128755/

Closes-Bug: #1380742
Change-Id: I3d48debc7d64f6a891ac37d4c2c5ebddfb5b00b0
'}]
commit_message:
Multipath commands with error messages in stdout fail to parse

This change fixes an issue in find_multipath_device() where the command
output of multipath -l <device> would sometimes fail to be parsed if
there were error messages in the stdout string in addition to the
expected output. We will now strip out the error messages before we
attempt to parse the lines.

NOTE(lyarwood): This is a simple port of the change already present
in Cinder for Kilo. This is no longer required on master for Nova due
to the move to os-brick.

Multipath commands with error messages in stdout fail to parse
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/128755/

Closes-Bug: #1380742

(2 comments)

Two nits inline but I don't really see anything here that is concerning to me at all.

I think calling it "manual cleaning", distinguished from "automatic cleaning" is incredibly valuable, and also helps make automatic cleaning easier to explain in the process.

My only questions are:
- Do we want to allow manual cleaning to be allowed to end the node in AVAILABLE, perhaps by providing arguments to the provide verb. I could see this being valuable for specific one-time-only configurations; but I'm also OK leaving it out as well.
- Can someone enable manual cleaning but not automatic cleaning? Today, it appears to be a single variable: https://github.com/openstack/ironic/blob/master/etc/ironic/ironic.conf.sample#L586. My suggestion would be to rename that variable to "automatically_clean_nodes" and enable manual cleaning without providing an option.'}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2015-10-07 14:17:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

(2 comments)

@Jay.

wrt manual cleaning going to AVAILABLE. That's a good question.

1. If manual cleaning ONLY went to AVAILABLE (instead of MANAGEABLE), it would have made the implementation a lot easier. BUT I think it definitely needs to be able to go to MANAGEABLE in case the operator wants to do other things before making it AVAILABLE.

2. We could have the default target stable state be MANAGEABLE, with an option to set the target's eventual target (eg in the CLI to set the provision state, 'target' == clean, 'target-stable-state' == AVAILABLE), but what does this mean? A. Do manual clean and skip any automated clean; B. Do manual clean and then automated clean


wrt enabling manual but not automated clean. The clean_nodes config is/was for automated cleaning, and I wasn't proposing to use that same config to enable/disable manual clean. Since manual clean is invoked explicitly by the user, I'm assuming they know what they are doing and that request overrides any config option. But that is a good point, maybe 'clean_nodes' should be renamed.

Question for you. I see that you refer to it as 'automatic clean' or 'automatically clean', vs 'automated clean' (I got that latter term from someone else). Do you have a preference? (I looked at a thesaurus and both 'automated' and 'automatic' are antonyms for 'manual'."}, {'account_id': 6618, 'date': '2015-10-07 17:25:06.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-07 17:49:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

commit_message:
Manual cleaning

Ironic already provides support for automated cleaning. This
specification describes support for manual cleaning, including an
API for operators to specify a list of clean steps to perform on a
node from the MANAGEABLE state.

Clean steps that are destructive and long running such as
configuring RAID or doing burn in, are good candidates for
manual cleaning instead of automated cleaning.

This feature was formerly called 'zapping'.

Change-Id: Iea975cfc2effc2d8be186294b88d85d8f2ace7b2
blueprint: manual-cleaning

commit_message:
Directive to check if Cinder Extensions are enabled

This creates a new directive that allows for the
HTML to check if a particular cinder extension is enabled.

Change-Id: I823cf721270fa25b321a9abca1d3e002fcd5c3e1
Partially-Implements: blueprint cinder-extensions.service

commit_message:
RDO: ensure rdo-release is not installed

Because rdo-release might already been provided by distros, we need to
make sure the package is not installed, otherwise this module will
install a repo maybe older than the one installed by rdo-release.

Example: if you try to install the kilo repo, the rdo-release will
install liberty (because it's the latest), so we need to make sure we
drop the package and let Puppet manage the repo.

Change-Id: I982853994d71b36266f50adf4f9da5395fe60dd2

commit_message:
Add/Remove the volume BDMs during resize

During resize instance migrate_disk_and_power_off should release
the existing volumes connected to the instance. Volume BDMS should
be disconnected and re-connected during finish_migrations. This is
required because manager terminates the prev volumes and
re-initializes the volumes again, which can lead to a new SCSI ID.

Change-Id: I9af2b16259dd98332c135b1870386c827d3c56d7
Closes-Bug: #1510235

As per reviewers' comments, there is no need to fix the intended behavior. That said, we should perhaps document it somewhere so that it's clear."}, {'account_id': 14591, 'date': '2015-11-02 19:09:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

So if you think that it is expected behavior probably we should remove that parameter from ml2_conf.ini file, additionally we should remove all parameters from each tunnel type configuration because they're not used anywhere - it suppose to be used right here."}]

commit_message:
Don't update metadata_proxy if metadata is not enabled

When enable_metadata_proxy is false, the agent instance will
not have metadata_driver. And agent should avoid using it.

Change-Id: Ia18dc5dea23de49b97c8f225532531eb9232fb51
Closes-Bug: #1510399
(cherry picked from commit ce3a31faff35e6f177bd747cf8427a9f00d05af0)

commit_message:
Use min and max on IntOpt option types

Latest version of oslo.config support the ability to set valid
range on IntOpt option values.  This path makes use of that feature
for a number of options with well known minimum and maximum values.

Change-Id: I5609a0553355bffba43f6e8fc77671e77ac4301a

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-13 09:41:15.000000000', 'message': 'Implementation of keepalived for haproxy

This commit uses a keepalived role, available in
ansible galaxy, to configure keepalived for haproxy

Keepalived makes the haproxy truely HA, by having
haproxy's VIP highly available between the hosts
defined in the inventory.

The keepalived role configuration is fully
documented on the upstream role.

To configure keepalived on your host, you only have to
give it a variable (dict). A template handles the
generation of the configuration of keepalived.

By default, the variable files defined in vars/configs/
are enough to have a keepalived working for haproxy,
with a master-backup configuration.

You can define other variable files by setting
haproxy_keepalived_(master|backup)_vars in your
user_variables. This should point to a "variable
template" file like the one you can find
in vars/configs/*

The haproxy playbook has been changed to rely on
the dynamic generation script. It will use the env.d
to have haproxy hosts. The first host from the
generated inventory will be considered as master,
while the others are slaves. The keepalived role
will only run if more than haproxy host is found
in the inventory. This behaviour can be changed
and keepalived can be disabled by the variable:
haproxy_use_keepalived.

The implemented variables are the following:
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_vip_cidr
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_interface
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_virtual_router_id
* haproxy_keepalived_priority_backup
* haproxy_keepalived_priority_master
* haproxy_keepalived_vars_file

In these variables, only the following variables
are necessary: keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_vip_cidr
However, it's recommended to also configure the
keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_interface
(to know which interface the vips can bind on)

Closes-Bug: 1414397
Change-Id: Ib87a3bb70d6f4b7ac9356e8a28fe4b5936eb9334
(cherry picked from commit a239b29baf21dc09570b55f45d86f70581841602)

commit_message:
Implementation of keepalived for haproxy

This commit uses a keepalived role, available in
ansible galaxy, to configure keepalived for haproxy

Keepalived makes the haproxy truely HA, by having
haproxy's VIP highly available between the hosts
defined in the inventory.

The keepalived role configuration is fully
documented on the upstream role.

To configure keepalived on your host, you only have to
give it a variable (dict). A template handles the
generation of the configuration of keepalived.

By default, the variable files defined in vars/configs/
are enough to have a keepalived working for haproxy,
with a master-backup configuration.

You can define other variable files by setting
haproxy_keepalived_(master|backup)_vars in your
user_variables. This should point to a "variable
template" file like the one you can find
in vars/configs/*

The haproxy playbook has been changed to rely on
the dynamic generation script. It will use the env.d
to have haproxy hosts. The first host from the
generated inventory will be considered as master,
while the others are slaves. The keepalived role
will only run if more than haproxy host is found
in the inventory. This behaviour can be changed
and keepalived can be disabled by the variable:
haproxy_use_keepalived.

The implemented variables are the following:
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_vip_cidr
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_interface
* haproxy_keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_virtual_router_id
* haproxy_keepalived_priority_backup
* haproxy_keepalived_priority_master
* haproxy_keepalived_vars_file

In these variables, only the following variables
are necessary: keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_vip_cidr
However, it's recommended to also configure the
keepalived_(ext|int)ernal_interface
(to know which interface the vips can bind on)

Closes-Bug: 1414397
Change-Id: Ib87a3bb70d6f4b7ac9356e8a28fe4b5936eb9334
(cherry picked from commit a239b29baf21dc09570b55f45d86f70581841602)

commit_message:
Use oslo.log instead of original logging

We are using oslo.log now, but some of the modules still use logging.
We should use oslo.log to keep consistency, besides, oslo.log can
provide fine wrapper for OpenStack projects.

Change-Id: Ibe57e503b88b39e284a9e4b11a1886cd4e8d4ccf

"deploy-all-in-one-node". All three of them was covering same topic and

commit_message:
Updated quickstart doc

I merged "quickstart" doc with "ansible-deployment" and
"deploy-all-in-one-node". All three of them was covering same topic and
added a lot of confusion for new users.

I added some clarification lines from myself, with main goal to recive one
straightforward document for new users.

In new doc I encourage to install kolla tools via pip, so user could get rid
of relative paths to config and scripts and run it from everythere.

Change-Id: I77a6ee14bca03e6ab008dbaf7ca76d9a939424e9
Related-Bug: #1512302

commit_message:
Use detail instead of explanation for 415 errors

As of webob 1.5.1 415 exception does not have explanation in it's
template. 'detail' is present in both versions templates.
Also adds CONTENT_TYPE to test-requests environment, to allow tests to
run correctly.

Change-Id: I52f2686ee838eef38ea9c5f48fe5f9e093e82412
Partial-Bug: #1512390

commit_message:
Remove resource_setup() from test_live_migration

The resource_setup() becomes meaningless, so let's remove it.

Change-Id: Id6de9b89aca0384e1e73a22ac39ff440cc15c097

commit_message:
Quote "bad" passwords in 'astute.yaml' right before upload it to nodes

Astute uses Ruby 2.1 with YAML 'Psych' engine which is not compatible
with Ruby 1.9 'Psych' engine used by Hierra in Puppet to parse unquoted
strings of passwords started with prefixed numeral values.

This commit uses alternate version of 'YAML::dump' method with forced
quotation of strings according its value and attributes.

Also this commit should fix possible problem with unquoted strings
containing bad mac-addresses which started with two zeros.

This commit should be reverted after upgrading to Ruby 2.1 everywhere.

Change-Id: I7435da01016c4b2266210eb9422ea1fae87de7f8
Closes-Bug: #1494779

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html

commit_message:
Use detail instead of explanation for 415 errors

As of webob 1.5.1 415 exception does not have explanation in it's
template. 'detail' is present in both versions templates.
Also adds CONTENT_TYPE to test-requests environment, to allow tests to
run correctly.

Change-Id: I52f2686ee838eef38ea9c5f48fe5f9e093e82412
Partial-Bug: #1512390

commit_message:
s/branch-designator/job-suffix/g

As clarkb suggested on #openstack-infra at 17:46 2015-10-22:
"maybe we should s/branch-designator/job-suffix/g in all those files
 as job-suffix makes more sense considering how branch-designator has been
 used".

The rename should make it easier for newcomers to understand
these jobs.

This renames branch-designator everywhere in jenkins/jobs/*.

Change-Id: Icb11271b958d92957fb9907ff03c0b898d7b76fc

commit_message:
Refactoring task detailed command

The output is classified into multiple inner methods.
  - _print_iterations_data
  - _print_task_info
  - _print_scenario_args
  - _print_summrized_result
  - _print_ssrs_result
  - _print_hints

Related: blueprint showing-summarized-result-in-system-readable
Change-Id: I09873d426c99f1eda505bf0c1adab2a8c9601ead

commit_message:
test_backend_sql work with python34

test_backend_sql was failing on python34 with two different errors.

1. On python3 we need encode unicode into byte before hashing.

...
    token_id_hash = hash_fn(token_id).hexdigest()
TypeError: Unicode-objects must be encoded before hashing

2. Delete one invalid testcase `test_non_ascii_init` since this testcase
is testing SQLAlchemy behavior rather than keystone, this testcase will also fail
on python3.

...
  File "/opt/stack/keystone/keystone/tests/unit/test_backend_sql.py",
  line 871, in test_non_ascii_init
    self.assertRaises(UnicodeDecodeError, FakeTable, col='')

3. Update the name of some generic methods since nose will capture the
keyword 'test' from the method and assume it is a testcase if there is.

bp python3
Change-Id: I68a8848ea2672efc206fdab0d29b32685678e3bf

[{'created': '2015-11-02 16:40:28.000000000', 'message': "    cinder-api-microversions

    Many changes to the Cinder REST API require changes to the consumers of the API.
    For example, If we need to add a required parameter to a method that is called
    by Nova, we'd need both the Nova calling code and the cinderclient that
    Nova uses to change. But newer Cinder versions with the change must work with
    older Nova versions, and there is no mechanism for this at the moment. Adding
    microversions will solve this problem.

    With microversions, the highest supported version will be negotiated by a field
    in the HTTP header that is sent to the Cinder API. In the case where the field
    'versions' is not sent (i.e. clients and scripts that pre-date this change),

    Cinder API v2 would be the default, and consumers of the API that wished to
    use a newer version could do so.

    Implements: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/cinder-api-microversions

commit_message:
cinder-api-microversions

    Many changes to the Cinder REST API require changes to the consumers of the API.
    For example, If we need to add a required parameter to a method that is called
    by Nova, we'd need both the Nova calling code and the cinderclient that
    Nova uses to change. But newer Cinder versions with the change must work with
    older Nova versions, and there is no mechanism for this at the moment. Adding
    microversions will solve this problem.

    With microversions, the highest supported version will be negotiated by a field
    in the HTTP header that is sent to the Cinder API. In the case where the field
    'versions' is not sent (i.e. clients and scripts that pre-date this change),
    then the lowest supported version would be used. This means that our current
    Cinder API v2 would be the default, and consumers of the API that wished to
    use a newer version could do so.

    Implements: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/cinder-api-microversions
    Change-Id: I2eb6b3aa86f8f6224dd223a8b8cef34ea15ce1e2

Change-Id: I9e738d27e0031d6bfc50111f39e8d7d1cc7dddd9

commit_message:
cinder-api-microversions

    Many changes to the Cinder REST API require changes to the consumers of the API.
    For example, If we need to add a required parameter to a method that is called
    by Nova, we'd need both the Nova calling code and the cinderclient that
    Nova uses to change. But newer Cinder versions with the change must work with
    older Nova versions, and there is no mechanism for this at the moment. Adding
    microversions will solve this problem.

    With microversions, the highest supported version will be negotiated by a field
    in the HTTP header that is sent to the Cinder API. In the case where the field
    'versions' is not sent (i.e. clients and scripts that pre-date this change),
    then the lowest supported version would be used. This means that our current
    Cinder API v2 would be the default, and consumers of the API that wished to
    use a newer version could do so.

    Implements: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/cinder-api-microversions
    Change-Id: I2eb6b3aa86f8f6224dd223a8b8cef34ea15ce1e2

Change-Id: I9d4ba204afb70b8b37ee87bfadbef4a6dbb075ec

commit_message:
Remove PEP8 exclusions

ATM H234,H302,H802,H405 are excluded from PEP8 checker. Those exclusions
must be eliminated in order to make the code correspond to the upstream
standards.

Change-Id: I25d8ba2f21ee228e8e5ee7a11822c43b38f3793b
Closes-bug: #1504352

Without interleave Pacemaker will consider memcached as a single

commit_message:
Ensure memcached resource uses interleave=true

Without interleave Pacemaker will consider memcached as a single
unit on all nodes so it will restart dependencies on every node in
case of failures.

More info at: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1262425

Change-Id: I284cbf33c8453a2abefc862f3d2e0b7f11ff4c3d

commit_message:
Allow scripts-library.sh to be sourced anywhere

Currently, we cannot source scripts-library.sh from anywhere outside of
the top-level of the openstack-ansible checkout.  This behaviour
changed with commit d9b9a427aa03f866458bdffc220c596c7b4b5bb2.

This commit itself updates scripts-library.sh to use $BASH_SOURCE to
find the location of os-detection.py, allowing scripts-library.sh to
be sourced from any external project without having to cd into the
openstack-ansible checkout and back out again.

Change-Id: Ia5cec5a0f1af4f8d4998465923077c87ffaf24ef
Closes-Bug: #1510443
